# .easignore — controls what EAS Build uploads. REPLACES .gitignore when present.
#
# Two invariants this file must honor:
#  1. Re-state every .gitignore exclusion — EAS ignores .gitignore once this file exists,
#     so anything omitted here (e.g. node_modules/) would otherwise be uploaded.
#  2. NEVER exclude a pnpm workspace package dir (apps/*, packages/*, scripts/orchestrator,
#     scripts/checks) nor the root pnpm-lock.yaml / pnpm-workspace.yaml / .npmrc. EAS runs
#     `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`, which validates every workspace importer; a missing
#     dir makes the lockfile look stale and breaks install. So we only trim NON-workspace,
#     non-build-time dirs to shrink the (China-network-sensitive) upload.
#
# NOTE: .easignore correctness can only be confirmed by a real `eas build` upload (no
# dry-run upload command exists). That validation lands with 子 plan 3's first preview build.

# --- re-stated from .gitignore (EAS reinstalls / regenerates these) ---
node_modules/
dist/
build/
out-tsc/
coverage/
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.production
.envrc
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
.obsidian/
*.swp
*.log
npm-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
.nx/cache
.nx/workspace-data
.nx/polygraph
.expo/
playwright-report/
playwright-test-results/
graphify-out/
.spec-kit/runs/
.claude/settings.local.json

# --- extra trims: non-workspace, not needed at build time ---
.git/
.github/
.claude/
.specify/
docs/
ops/
specs/
